{@--1@} An iron (or wooden)
beam or bar used for locking or
shutting a gate {#(argala)#}; {#ekaH kftsnAM#}
{#nagarapariGaprAMSubAhurBunakti#} <ls>Ś. 2. 15</ls>;  
<ls>R. 16. 84</ls>; <ls>Śi. 19. 32</ls>; <ls>M. 5. 2.</ls>

{@--2@}
(Hence) A bar barrier, hindrance,
obstacle; {#BArgavasya sukfto'pi so'#} 
{#BavatsvargamArgapariGo duratyayaH#} <ls>R. 11. 88.</ls>

{@--3@}
A stick or club studded or tipped
with iron; <ls>R. 12. 73.</ls>

{@--11@}
A line of clouds crossing the sun at
sunrise or sunset.

({%<ab>m.</ab>%}
dual) Two birds flying on each side
of a traveller (regarded as an omen).
